rComments: She is definitely not an easy professor. You have to work hard, make sure that you do all the problems she suggests to work on after each class. Her tests and final exams were heavy, but she is super understanding of arithmetic/calculation errors. However all your steps must be correct. I would recommend her if you love challenging classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She records the sessions which is the only good thing about her course. She took three tests throughout the semester and all of them were so hard which makes it impossible to get full marks. I recommend not to take her course at all.

Since this is a high level course I think its not fair to expect perfections. However, sometimes she wasn't able to answer the questions in the class. The worst part of her course are the tests. They are so long containing around 24 questions, and you have 3 hours to solve them!!!! Don't take a course with her if you do have another choice.

This was a really fun class in my opinion and Professor Sajna taught it really well. All of the tests and the final exam were open book and questions were similar to examples from class. She is not an easy professor but if you keep up with the recommended exercises, you should be good!

5 tests throughout the semster, each test 3 hours long and graded very harshly. Gives no part marks and makes it impossible to get full mark on ANY question. Final exam was super hard with too many questions and not enough time to complete.
Terrible professor. Exteremely hard exams and harsh grading, almost guaranteed to fail. Will never be taking any classes with her again.
The worst math professor that I've had the displeasure of having. Gives no part marks on tests (either 0 or full mark for a question). Don't take her class.
Her exams are fair and she's patient.

Sajna's midterms and exams are almost identical to her tests from previous years, and she posts all of her old tests on brightspace. If you just memorize how to solve the questions on those old tests, then you'll easily get an A+.

This is a really tough class but Prof. Sajna was super helpful in explaining the concepts during office hours anytime I was confused. The assignments are really challenging, but you get used to them as the semester goes on. I would recommend her as long as you're up for the challenge of this class.
Amazing prof. Do the homework questions and especially the questions at dgd's to prepare for the midterms and finals.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: She is clearly knowledgeable about the subject but sometimes isn't able to explain the topics well to the class. Her marking scheme is very forgiving though and she is accessible outside of the classroom.
Great teacher! Expectations were always clear going into the exams and she drops a ton of hints about what will be on the midterms. It does take a ton of studying to do well regardless, though!

You can lose entire marks on midterms and exams from making little mistakes like forgetting to put the C after you integrate or if your signs are wrong, skipping notations, etc... Do not take her unless you have no choice

I would never take a class with her again. Her expectations are not clear and the assignments are very hard. She expects you to be able to program without ever teaching it or it being a prerequisite for the course.

- She is teaching graph theory, but she is tough graded for each ass. and exam.  - No flexibility, NO helpful. -Don't take any class with her - she doesn't care at all for students effort and their working hard.

She explains the material really well. She writes everything on the board by hand so be prepared to take a lot of notes. She is also a very stingy grader. I would recommend taking this class with her as other students from other sections would attend our lectures. Her exams are brutal, however.

She's organized and clearly explains the material; however, she moves through the material very, very quickly. Together, the exams are worth 90% of your grade, and they're hard. You should never skip her lectures or the DGDs. You don't need the textbook. She sometimes treats us, collectively, like children, which is a bit weird but not malicious.
I better not say how horrible she is as a prof, work yourself and give it a 100% you'll ace it
She's like your elementary school teacher. You know, the one you disliked for being too strict, but deep down you know she also taught you how to add and subtract.

She is organized and very knowledgeable. However, she moves so quickly through material in class that it's hard to write, listen, and understand the abstract concepts all at the same time. She does a good job preparing her TAs, so I'd suggest attending the DGDs. The tests are hard, and they're 90% of your grade.
Knowledgable and helpful. Hard work is to be expected, that's why we're here :)
Excellent lecturer and makes expectations clear.  Very stringent marker and does not appreciate students walking into lectures late.
Stingiest professor ever. Great lecturer, and very helpful during office hours. Assignments were easy, midterms were ok expect for the multiple choice section.

I took a few classes with Dr. Sajna. She's the most amazing professor I have ever had! She explains everything so clearly. Assignments and exams reflect the class material very well. I was her TA for the MAT1348 DGD later,  she went over each question  with me to make sure I would convey  the right solutions to the students. She's very responsible!

Really clear professor. Comparable with an excellent highschool teacher. The course itself is a combination of the easiest philosophy course PHI1101) and grade 12 data (MDM4U). Teacher is willing to help you at any time, and everything on exams is taught in class. The class is relatively based around logic, so actually think in it. Duh.
Great prof. She gives great notes and is pretty good for helping you in office hours.  Really nice person, and love to help you out if your putting an effort in.

An Okay Prof, fairly helpful if you go see her, if you put in the work its not a hard course, if you do not put in a lot of work it will be extremly hard, go to all classes and the DGD's and work on the assignments early as you will likely have trouble on them as the course progresses

Exam weight is so high (60%)!!  The exam difficulty level was higher than the midterm, with some slightly unexpected questions. Nitpicky marking; she really is not flexible with her grading.. Makes you feel like you are back in high school when you have to listen to her rants against students walking in late/asking about exam questions, etc.

Her teaching is fine, but she has zero flexibility with grading, she doesn't look out for the students interest and she doesn't care at all if the student is working hard or not everything to her is numbers! I would highly avoid her.
She tries very hard to explain things clearly.  She responds to emails quickly.  The exams are kept simple despite the trickiness of this course.

Extremely nice and helpful professor. Exams are very fair and won't present any surprises IF you do the suggested exercises and attend all the lectures. Communicates the material very well and is approachable outside class. Highly recommended.

She taught the class very well and explains things very clearly. I thought the midterm was tough(very low average) but the final was VERY fair. Takes the best n-1 assignments which is nice.Typically starts every class reviewing key concepts and definitions. Content is difficult at times so pay attention. I recommend her.
Don't take any class with her if you have a choice.

She is a really good prof, explains things really clearly, and is devoted in teaching this course. However she is quite intolerable when people talk. More importantly, she is a hard marker and her midterm and final exam were quite hard. With her, you really got to understand the material very well, plus 1348 can get difficult in some areas.

She is a really good prof, explains things really clearly, and is devoted in teaching this course. However she is quite intolerable when people talk. More importantly, she is a hard marker and her midterm and final exam were quite hard. With her, you really got to understand the material very  well, plus 1348 can get difficult in some areas.

Really 'anal' marker. You gotta explain every step in complete detail. Sometimes you wonder whether this is a math class or an English class. She wants you to write essays in your midterm/final when you're solving and if you don't do that, you will lose marks. Great prof, HARD marker.
She teaches a course she found in a cereal box. Riddles and mazes about knights and knaves are about all you'll get from this escapade. And man, she wears some shiny pants.
40% of class failed, she is good with teaching but very hard with marking, better aviod

Good prof. Teaches you till the last second of class (never got out early). I though assignments should be a free 10% of my final grade, obviously not the case in this class.  Midterms are moderate difficulty, but they're fair.
Good teacher, but this was first time she taught class.  Presentations were boring, and too much time spent on Greek math.  Nice person.
ahhh she talks to you like your 2 years old and "special" i cant stand it

I really liked her class. She knows what she's teaching and tries 120% of her best to help you excel in the class. BUT she's very strict in marking. Listen to what she says in class and follow exactly otherwise she WILL take your mark away.
